metadata.name: #001 修験道の妖狐　Shugendo Yoko(yokai fox)
metadata.description:
旅人の無事を祈りながら、自らも山で修行する四尾の妖狐。

While praying for the safety of travelers, the four-tailed Yoko practices asceticism in the mountains herself.

Shugendō; Japanese mountain asceticism incorporating Shinto and Buddhist concepts.
The person who does shugendo practice is called a shugensha or yamabushi.
